latestIgtvVideos.title: Trying Morphe, Rare Beauty and Nars😮
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
FINAL VERDICT✨
❤️ @morphebrushes Eyeshadow Palette in 35G and Truth or Bare.
I'm in love with the shades in the 35G palette. It's a one stop palette for people who love warm shades (I'm one of them😉) 
•Coming to the eyeshadow application-I witnessed no patchiness, the colour payoff is incredible. The shades however are a bit powdery- I did experience some fall out in the palette, but not on my face!
•I used the nude shade to set my cut-crease concealer and surprisingly it did not crease my concealer even a bit!!!😫
-Would I buy more Morphe Palettes? HELL YEAH. They are incredible for the price you pay.
❤️ @rarebeauty Foundation Shade- 280N (I could've gone a shade lighter)
I am Amazed with how flawless my base turned out. The foundation seems to be of Medium Coverage but you can definitely build it up. It's perfect for a dry skin person but an Oily skin person can make it work as well since The foundation is not thick, it's smooth, lightweight and just incredible to work with!
❤️Rare Beauty Blush- Shade Joy (Radiant Finish)
Holy Mother of God I have no words for this blush. It's insanely pigmented- 2 tiny dots per side did the job for me! 
I thought it might move the layers below it (the foundation and concealer) since it's so dewy, but it did not! A 1000 points for not making my makeup patchy!
❤️ Nars Radiant Creamy Concealer- Shade Ginger
This concealer is great, not drying at all, since Drying out my undereyes is a problem I face with a lot of concealers. However, in my opinion as good as this concealer is, it's not absolutely necessary to own it. There are lots of concealers in the market that'll do the job at a lesser price!
@nykaabeauty @mynykaa
